The '''Silver Medal of the [[Zoological Society of London]]''' is "Awarded to a Fellow of the Society or any other person for contributions to the understanding and appreciation of zoology, including such activities as public education in natural history, and wildlife conservation."<ref>http://www.zsl.org/science/scientific-awards/</ref> It was first awarded in 1847.<ref>http://pdmedallions.co.uk/Commerce/product_info.php?products_id=783</ref>
